{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SafariUI\/documentation\/SafariUI\/WebAuthentication\/init(url:callbackURLScheme:completionHandler:)"],"title":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SafariUI\/documentation\/SafariUI\/WebAuthentication\/CompletionHandler"],"title":"Type Aliases"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/safariui\/webauthentication"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A wrapper for "},{"code":"ASWebAuthenticationSession","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in SwiftUI","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:17WebAuthenticationAAV","title":"WebAuthentication","symbolKind":"struct","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"WebAuthentication","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":[{"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"14.0","name":"iOS","unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"14.0","beta":false,"name":"Mac Catalyst","deprecated":false},{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"visionOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"1.0"}],"modules":[{"name":"SafariUI"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"WebAuthentication"}],"roleHeading":"Structure"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SafariUI\/documentation\/SafariUI\/WebAuthentication"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SafariUI\/documentation\/SafariUI"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"WebAuthentication"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use a "},{"code":"WebAuthentication","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance to authenticate a user through a web service, including one run by a third party. Initialize the session with a URL that points to the authentication webpage. When the user starts the authentication session, the operating system shows a modal view telling them which domain the app is authenticating with and asking whether to proceed. If the user proceeds with the authentication attempt, a browser loads and displays the page, from which the user can authenticate. In iOS, the browser is a secure, embedded web view. In macOS, the system opens the user’s default browser if it supports web authentication sessions, or Safari otherwise.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On completion, the service sends a callback URL to the session with an authentication token. The session passes this URL back to the app through a completion handler. "},{"code":"AuthenticationSession","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ensures that only the calling app’s session receives the authentication callback, even when more than one app registers the same callback URL scheme.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WebAuthentication"},{"type":"text","text":" is not a normal SwiftUI view. Unlike "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SafariUI\/documentation\/SafariUI\/SafariView"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"must"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" be presented using one of the following included view modifiers:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SafariUI\/documentation\/SafariUI\/SwiftUI\/View\/webAuthentication(_:webAuthentication:)-74m38","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SafariUI\/documentation\/SafariUI\/SwiftUI\/View\/webAuthentication(_:webAuthentication:)-5x82p","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SafariUI\